  "body": "In our efforts to support various L2s, we have found that many of these protocols rely on ethers definitions for things like signers and providers. Truffle does not seem to deeply support ethers, defaulting in many cases to web3.js. We need to fix this!\n\n- [ ] Audit everywhere the Truffle code relies on web3js\n- [ ] Scope out the changes needed to support ethers in addition\n- [ ] Implement ",
